contact network within the LS resembles a liquid-like state. An unsteadiness of\nthe LS has been uncovered wherein the interface (between the floating-cluster\nand the dilute gas underneath) and the top of the bed are found to oscillate\nsinusoidally, with its oscillation frequency closely matching with the\nfrequency of external shaking.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Apr 2016 05:25:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-18"}
